-- Quas<br>
<br>
Will clerics even take a non-cleric’s suggestion seriously? I know one showed she won’t. For every suggestion tossed around there’s a reason why it won’t work: There’s no way to check everything’s done up to Rage--why bother asking the question?; You can cast Identify, but can you trust the caster?; Why should we re-roll?; Why should we random?; It’s not my fault you didn’t know about the list sooner…don’t try to bump me now, it’s my turn!<br>
<br>
“They run it as fair as possible (and if you don’t believe it's fair... then tell me how Fucktards like Prizmo and Mlain can get on it), and they enforce it.”<br>
-- Quas<br>
<br>
Fair is subject to opinion it comes to the list. You cannot quantify it. No one wants to even broach the idea of truncating the list by placing requirements on it. The slightest modification could topple guild support and lead to finger pointing by clerics like Prizmo and Mlain. IMO, most people would rather their ‘toon warm a spot for a few weeks than dwell on the subject of fairness, which has been brought up here over and over. That being said, I would still prefer it if someone had the balls to hit the breaks and say, “You, you, and you, you’re moved to the back, you don’t have everything up to Rage. You, &lt;insert asshole cleric&gt;, you damn well aren’t going to see Rage until everyone’s done.” Some discrimination is better than none. <br>
<br>
“People whine the Quellious is FFA, and why is that?”<br>
-- Quas<br>
<br>
I’m not one of the whiners. General chaos did not ensue whenever Alliance entered NToV or HoT. <br>
<br>
“And who are they? I'll tell you that too. They are the people with the power to enforce their decisions. Well now... the clerics just showed up with a bigger force, and THEY are taking charge and making the policy when it comes to Rage.”<br>
-- Quas<br>
<br>
They were also the guilds to monopolize spawns. Same deal with clerics now. That they use this mob for their epic somehow makes it better?<br>
<br>
“Not everyone is supposed to have an epic. So if Joe Cleric has to wait 6 months, and then spend every day in Skyfire for 3-5 weeks prior to his/her turn, then why should anyone be exempt?”<br>
-- Quas<br>
<br>
Why do you or anyone get to decide Joe Cleric has to wait 6 months according to this list? Why do you get to decide he is in the wrong if he sits there for days, triggers, and kills Rage, bypassing the list?<br>
<br>
“No buts, STFU... cause I'm tired of hearing you whining.”<br>
<br>
Thanks Quas for the display of attitude responsible for moving this thread from the General forum.<br>
<br>
That’s it…I’m not going to quote anyone else. I’m sure good points have been made on the pro and anti side. I am not a demon anarchist trying to singe clerics with the sharp and scalding end of my pitchfork. Rage is monopolized. It doesn’t sit well with me, doesn’t diminish the inherit wrong no matter what the “reasons” and “VI justifications” behind it. When the list was agreed upon by a few they didn’t automatically run out and announce the new de facto entitlement they were reserving for themselves, else they would've been laughed out of town. They served their best interests by approaching friends and guild mates with the idea, people likely to agree back with them and further gain support to enforce their desires instead of doing the right thing, the “fair” thing, and making as much noise as possible before assigning numbers. I’ve only noticed Belhaven take it upon himself to make some noise. That’s more than I can say for most that claim to care so much.<br>
<br>
Dum loquimur, fugerit invida Aetas: carpe diem, quam minimum credula postero.<br>
