In any case it's only a monopoly inasmuch as they will try to make bucking it untenable. Hopefully too difficult to bother with, but nevertheless not impossible. Possible to compete means it can't be a monopoly. But they don't have to make it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> easy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and hopefully they won't.<br>
<br>
It's really not a monopoly but a coop. You can try to sell your corn outside of the coop but the coop will collude to undercut you until you either join also or go out of business. Possibly a big conglomerate (uberguild) can come and challenge the coop, but the coop can at least hopefully at least <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> survive</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. If the coop is maintaining a fair price and only trying to keep the farmers in business in a fair way they probably will last. If the coop becomes corrupted or starts gauging then they open themselves to being wiped out by the conglomerates.<br>
